\subsection*{Activity 10.2: Motion of an airplane}
An airplane is traveling in a pattern described by the parametric equations
\[x = 4 t , \quad  y = -t^4 + 4t - 1 ,\]
where $x$ and $y$ have units of miles, and $t$ is in hours. 
\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
    \item Find the slope of the curve $C$ at any point $(x,y)$
    \item Prove that $(0,-1)$ lies on the curve $C$. 
    \item What is the slope of the curve at $(0,-1)$?
    \item Write the equation of the tangent line to the curve at $(0,-1)$.
    \item Suppose that the control tower is 5 miles east of the origin. At what point in the plane is the control tower positioned?  
    \item Write an equation that, when solved, will allow you to figure out at what point will the airplane by flying directly toward the control tower. To answer this question, think geometrically about what does it mean to be flying directly toward a point. You will want to express the idea of slope in two ways: in terms of the slope of the tangent line at a point and in terms of the slope of a line through the curve and the control tower.
    \item (Challenge) Solve the equation and find when the plane is directly pointing towards the control tower.

\end{enumerate}




\defn{If $C (x)$ is the cost of producing $x$ items and $R(x)$ is the revenue from selling $x$ items, then \begin{itemize}
    \item $C'(x) $ is the marginal cost,
    \item $R'(x)$ is the marginal revenue,
    \item $P(x) = R(x) - C(x)$ is the profit function. $P'(x)$ is the marginal profit.
\end{itemize}}


\subsection*{Activity 10.3: Cost, revenue, and profit I}

The manager of a computer shop has to decide how many computers to store in the back of the shop. If she stores a large number, she has to pay
extra in storage costs. If she stores only a small number, she will have to reorder
more often, which will involve additional handling costs. She has found that if she
stores $x$ computers, the storage and handling costs for a year will
be $C$ dollars, where
\[ C(x) = 10x^{3}-900x^{2}+16000x+210000\]

\begin{enumerate}[(a)]
    \item What is the fixed cost of the computer shop? In practical terms this may account for rent and utilities expenses.
\item What is the marginal cost?
\item What does the marginal cost function look like?
\item Now suppose that $x$ computers give revenue $R(x) = 1000x$. What is the marginal revenue? What is the real world interpretation of your finding?
\item Find a formula for the profit function $P(x)$.
\item Find the marginal profit using the marginal revenue and the marginal cost.
\item What does the marginal profit function look like?
\item When is the profit increasing? When is it decreasing?

\end{enumerate}

